```
## 2. Takens embedding```


Cell 4:
```
import sys
sys.path.insert(0, '..')
from src.sliding_window import takens_embedding

dimension = 3
time_delay = 8
stride = 10

embedded = takens_embedding(signal, dimension, time_delay, stride)
print(f'Embedded point cloud shape: {embedded.shape}')

from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import Axes3D
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection='3d')
ax.scatter(embedded[:, 0], embedded[:, 1], embedded[:, 2], alpha=0.7)
ax.set_xlabel('x(t)')
ax.set_ylabel('x(t+tau)')
ax.set_zlabel('x(t+2*tau)')
ax.set_title('Takens embedding: periodic signal traces an ellipse')
plt.show()```


Cell 5:
```
## 3. Persistent homology on embedded point cloud```


Cell 6:
```
import ripser
import persim

result = ripser.ripser(embedded, maxdim=1)
dgms = result['dgms']

print('H0 points:', len(dgms[0]))
print('H1 points:', len(dgms[1]))

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 6))
persim.plot_diagrams(dgms, ax=ax, show=False)
ax.set_title('Persistence diagram (Takens embedding of periodic signal)')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()```


